screenshots.title: Eternal Fall
screenshots.description: Eternal Fall, where the Autumn lasts forever. There are many mushrooms and the ground is covered in leaves that fall from the trees. The Eternal fall is home of the Autumn Court.

screenshots.title: Quest Screen
screenshots.description: When you summon a pixie, you are bound to their Court! Try interacting with your pixie after you summoned one, if possible try to gain their trust by doing Quests!

screenshots.title: Frozen Retreat
screenshots.description: The Frozen Retreat is the home of the Winter Court. Lakes are frozen and there are Ice Spikes. The undead are more present in this biome.

screenshots.title: Library
screenshots.description: The Library can be found in forest or plains all over the Feywild. If you ever loose your Feywild Lexicon, just ring the bell and a librarian will help you out!

screenshots.title: Golden Seelie Fields
screenshots.description: The Golden Seelie Fields are the home of the Summer Fey. It's rich with summer flowers and giant Sunflower. The area is patrolled by many bees.

screenshots.title: Librarian

data.name: The Afterlight
data.summary: Delve into a forgotten realm stuck in a blue moon.

screenshots.title: The Glowing Caves
screenshots.description: A cave biome with a varying amount of glowing plants and crystals, providing a decent amount of underground light. This makes the biome a relatively safe place to be.

screenshots.title: The Bloodweed Caves
screenshots.description: A hostile and dark cave biome that spawns crimson skeletons within. Bloodberries grow in this biome as well.

screenshots.title: The Moonlight Lowlands
screenshots.description: A biome in the dimension with twisting plants and glowing crystal spires.

screenshots.title: The Moonlight Swamp
screenshots.description: A dark biome in the dimension with small lakes and plants.

screenshots.title: Moonlight Highlands
screenshots.description: A very dark biome with hardly any glowing plants, and harbors many monsters, thus making it by far the most dangerous biome. Also very high up!

screenshots.title: The Dark Skeleton Mob
screenshots.description: Another hostile mob that is stronger than the average moonspawn but doesn't spawn very often.

screenshots.title: The Moon Fox Mob
screenshots.description: Moon foxes are herbivores and eat certain nearby plants.

screenshots.title: The Verdant Caves
screenshots.description: A dark cave biome full of lush green, spiced up by various flora.

screenshots.title: Scuttlebugs
screenshots.description: Scuttlebugs are passive, but they can wither their attackers. They are very rare spawns.

screenshots.title: The Aqua Caves
screenshots.description: A peaceful cave biome that does not house any hostile mobs, despite being darker than the glowing caves.

screenshots.title: The Moonlight Forest
screenshots.description: A biome in the dimension where the player is safe from most dangers.

screenshots.title: The Moonspawn Mob
screenshots.description: One of the two hostile mobs in the dimension. This one is similar to a husk.

screenshots.title: The Shadow Forest
screenshots.description: An extremely dark surface biome where gloomy thick trees will grow and thrive. Comes in two types, the Shadow Forest and the Shadow Mire.

screenshots.title: The Shadow Caves
screenshots.description: A gloomy cave biome full of infesting weeds and blooms.

screenshots.title: A Afterlight Shrine in the overworld
screenshots.description: Special shrines that can be used to get the portal block and portal igniter to the dimension.

data.name: Craft Tools From Anything
data.summary: Allows you to craft tools and armor from literally any existing item in the vanilla game.

data.name: Nekoration
data.summary: A Decoration Mod For Minecraft

screenshots.title: Palette
screenshots.description: Palette is necessary when you edit a painting and serves as a color picker

screenshots.title: Stone Blocks
screenshots.description: A stone wall containing all variants of Nekoration's stone blocks

screenshots.title: Furniture
screenshots.description: Square tables, round tables and sittable chairs, made from different types of planks(except pumpkin ones :P). Those recipes are not conflicting with most(probably all) other furniture mods, so you can feel free to put 'em together

screenshots.title: Quartz Doors
screenshots.description:
Doors and taller doors made from quartz 
(they can also be colored with dyes)

screenshots.title: Easel Menus
screenshots.description: easel menus can be used to display both items and colorful texts

screenshots.title: Neko Brochure
screenshots.description: An encyclopedia describing and explaining all aspects of Nekoration. (Work in Progress)

screenshots.title: Wallpaper
screenshots.description: Any banner can be made into wallpaper, and can then be pasted onto your walls!

screenshots.title: Colorful Stone Blocks
screenshots.description: you can tint any stone block with any vanilla dye, to make it colorful

screenshots.title: And... who knows what'll be the next update?
screenshots.description: Nekoration is still updating actively and will keep adding new stuff. So stay tuned, and always be ready for upcoming updates! : )

screenshots.title: Window Blocks
screenshots.description: Many different types of window blocks, each with variants of different wood types

screenshots.title: Poster
screenshots.description: a poster for Nekoration (screenshot taken with the mod's first release)

screenshots.title: Paintings
screenshots.description: This feature is still being worked on but it's almost there. You can draw pictures or load png images as your paintings, and share 'em with your friends!

screenshots.title: Half-Timber Blocks & Pillars
screenshots.description: The image here shows only a few examples. half-timber really has a looooot of variants since it can have different wood types, colors and patterns

screenshots.title: Window Top & Window Sill
screenshots.description: They can be used to replace the top and bottom parts of window frame, or can be used separately above or below windows as you like

screenshots.title: Custom Blocks
screenshots.description: They can be turned into other blocks by a right click with other blocks in your hand. And their rotation and position are adjustable using corresponding tools

screenshots.title: Small Decorations
screenshots.description: Other small decorations: flowering plants, candle holders, etc (you can light the candles with a torch or lantern, and use their 'soul' variants if you want the flame to be blue)

screenshots.title: Half-Timber Selector
screenshots.description: The selector that will show up in 'Wooden Blocks' tab in Creative Inventory, helping you select block by wood types (Just ignore those 2 JEI buttons at the bottom XP)

screenshots.title: Window Frame
screenshots.description: You can make a frame around a window to make it look nicer
